<big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big><big>
Looking for a studio or one bedroom for two people plus small dog. Preferable $1200 - $1400. Would like to move in asap and would want to live in Staten Island. Utilities included as well would help a lot. Please help I need to move urgently. Serious inquiries. No fees either </big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big></big><br><br></big></big></big>I am a dog sitter through Rover, and I am also a photographer. I love what I do! I am a mama in a wheelchair fully independent, and I have 2 boys (age 8 and 9) that I share with their father and their other mom, but we're in separate households. I am currently in a neighborhood that I don't feel safe in, so I really want to move elsewhere. I no longer want to have to worry about what could happen when I'm outside with my boys even in broad daylight. I am in a wheelchair but all I would need is access into the home. I don't need wheelchair accessible shower/bath, lower countertops or anything like that. A fenced in yard for the boys and Rover dogs to play in would be so great. Since I am in a wheelchair, I'll only be watching small to medium size dogs. The boys are super sweet. They are full of energy but know when to settle down, especially at night and know not to be too loud before a certain time in the morning. I would like a place outside of Portland, but depending on the area, I'll consider a place in Portland. The closer to Troutdale the better, since that is where the boys other home is. If you have any questions at all, please let me know.

I lived in a mother in law suite before and my rent was mostly paid by doing childcare Monday through Friday for the family I rented from. This could be an option if you have children and would like for them to be watched during the Summer, before and after school.

Ideally I’m looking for a part of the week rental in Manhattan. I’ve done hotels and other solutions but it’s such a hassle, I'd prefer to stay in the same place every time so I know the neighborhood, train options and I can store my things since I will be returning to city each week.

My situation looks like this: I’d be coming up from Philly to NYC on Tuesday and leaving Thursday every week for at least 4 months due to the return to the office program. I’m open to a room or an entire place. The idea would be that you can take the complementary nights to my schedule so we can both split a lease. That way you can stay in the place from Thursday nights to Monday nights. Does that make sense to you? I can be flexible on the nights we will split but definitely I need to split.

Does anyone need a place for part of the week each week for work and want to split a lease with me being ghost roommates? That way we occupy the same place every week but without sharing it, we are all happy, saving money, and having a private space

This Ad is for OWNERS only, no agents! I am in great need of a cheap small Studio preferably in the basement to move in immediately in Staten Island close to Brooklyn. I am without a home right now and want to find a landlord who is understanding. Email me if you have anything available.
looking for room swap possibilities between berlin &lt;-&gt; NYC last two weeks of sep 22 (+- flexible). in exchange you'll get my bedroom in a shared flat in Neukölln, Berlin. this flat is a catch: 150m2 with open kitchen and living room + terrace with same area, right in front of the canal. shared with 4 other amazing people. mandatory videocall for potential candidates. bipoc and queer friendly
Hi! I'm grad student in my mid-20s looking for a room in the $650-$900 ish range for this upcoming school year (Aug-May) or semester (Aug-Jan). I have great credit, some provable income and a guarantor if needed as well.

My classes are in Downtown Brooklyn so something easily accessible to there by bus or train would be ideal. Crown Heights, Clinton Hill, Bed-Stuy, PLG, etc. I am very flexible with location though if you are a little more out there still hmu.

I am very clean, quiet and will mostly be out at school, work or events. I am not much of a party animal and don't drink so when I do go out at night I tip toe straight to my room. An ideal home would be 420 friendly as but I can adapt if that is not ideal. I am queer and brown so roommates must be tolerant of that.

That is about it from me! If you have a spot and would like more information or social media links from me feel free to shoot me an e-mail, I check it v regularly. If you do contact me pls share a little bit about the room, apartment and roommates.
    

